## Installation

This script requires Python 3.9+ and the following packages:

- numpy
- pandas

You can install the dependencies with:

```bash
pip install numpy pandas

I strongly suggest you to create a venv before installing the packages, as it follows:
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate   # On Windows: .venv\Scripts\activate
pip install numpy pandas

After collecting our experimental data, is it possibile to run the script using
python mc_ionic_strength.py \
  --mass-mean 8.20e-4 \
  --mass-sd   1.0e-5  \
  --Vtot-mean 1.00e-1 \
  --Vtot-sd   5.0e-4  \
  --CHCl-mean 1.00e-3 \
  --CHCl-sd   1.0e-5  \
  --VHCl-mean 1.00e-2 \
  --VHCl-sd   1.0e-4  \
  --pH-mean   4.00    \
  --pH-sd     0.02    \
  --pKa-mean  4.76    \
  --pKa-sd    0.02    \
  --N         200000  \
  --seed      123     \
  --out-prefix "acetate_pH4_ionic_strength"

where:
	•	mass-mean, mass-sd
Mean and standard deviation of the mass of NaOAc (g).
	•	Vtot-mean, Vtot-sd
Mean and standard deviation of the final solution volume (L).
	•	CHCl-mean, CHCl-sd
Mean and standard deviation of the HCl concentration (mol/L).
	•	VHCl-mean, VHCl-sd
Mean and standard deviation of the HCl volume added (L).
	•	pH-mean, pH-sd
Mean and standard deviation of the measured pH of the buffer.
	•	pKa-mean, pKa-sd
Mean and standard deviation of the acetic acid pKₐ.
	•	N
Number of Monte Carlo simulations.
	•	seed
Seed for the random number generator (for reproducibility).
	•	out-prefix
Prefix for output files.
